HEADWORD: Lissencephala
<hw>Lis`sen*ceph"a*la</hw>
<pr>(l⟦icr⟧s`s⟦ecr⟧n*s⟦ecr⟧f"⟦adot⟧*l⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>lisso`s</grk> smooth + <grk>'egke`falos</grk>
the brain.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A general name for all those
placental mammals that have a brain with few or no cerebral
convolutions, as Rodentia, Insectivora, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
